UID:fMtf3jWOImz6TIbvNFKM7
SUMMARY:BE LOUD Breakfast
DTSTAMP:20260317T070146Z
DTSTART:20260317T150000Z
DESCRIPTION:Description Join us for the BE LOUD Breakfast\, an annual fundr
	aising event for the King County Sexual Assault Resource Center \\(KCSARC\
	\). This year&'s event is especially meaningful as 2026 marks the 50th ann
	iversary of KCSARC. For fifty years\, KCSARC has empowered survivors and c
	ommunities. This incredible milestone is a testament to you-our community.
	 You have shown up\, spoken out\, and stood with survivors every step of t
	he way. Today\, we face new and urgent challenges. But our mission remains
	 unwavering. Together\, we will keep moving forward-LOUDER than ever befor
	e. Will you BE LOUD with us? Register now at donate.kcsarc.org/BELOUD26\n\
	nhttps://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/be-loud-breakfast/18089678/
	2026-03-17T00\n\nFrom SEAtoday - Food & Drink
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/be-loud-breakfast/1808967
	8/2026-03-17T00
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:seatoday-food
CATEGORIES:SEAtoday - Food & Drink
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT1H
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:RSgJV2_vufMmUkCC4EAnF
SUMMARY:Coworking Tuesdays
DTSTAMP:20260317T070146Z
DTSTART:20260317T163000Z
DESCRIPTION:Tuesday Cowork \\+ Coffee/Tea \\(Weekly\\) \n\nNeed a reason to
	 get out of your inbox cave and into a productive\, low-pressure space? Jo
	in us every Tuesday for a drop-in coworking morning—bring your laptop\, kn
	ock out your priorities\, and enjoy the energy of working alongside other 
	local professionals. \n\nWhen: Tuesdays | 9:30–11:30 AM | No registration 
	needed\n\nFormat: Come for the full two hours or pop in when you can\n\nWh
	o it’s for: Business owners\, remote workers\, creatives\, students\, nonp
	rofit leaders—anyone who wants focused work time \\+ light community\n\nWh
	at to expect: Quiet “get-it-done” work blocks\, optional hellos \\+ quick 
	intros\, and a friendly vibe \\(no forced networking\\) \n\nLocation \\(th
	rough February\\): Bothell Visitor Center\n\nWe’ll rotate locations monthl
